Rapports annuels 1996|publisher=[[Ultratop]]|language=French|accessdate=May 3, 2019}}</ref>\n|76\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Canada Top Singles (''RPM'')<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bac-lac.gc.ca/eng/discover/films-videos-sound-recordings/rpm/Pages/image.aspx?Image=nlc008388.9730&URLjpg=http%3a%2f%2fwww.collectionscanada.gc.ca%2fobj%2f028020%2ff4%2fnlc008388.9730.gif&Ecopy=nlc008388.9730|title=RPM Year End Top 100 Hit Tracks|work=[[RPM (magazine)|RPM]]|publisher=[[Library and Archives Canada]]|accessdate=May 3, 2019}}</ref>\n|61\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Europe (Eurochart Hot 100)<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/hd2/IDX-Business/Music/Archive-Music-Media-IDX/IDX/90s/96/MM-1996-12-21-OCR-Page-0012.pdf#search=%22nirvana%20about%20girl%22|title=Eurochart Hot 100 Singles 1996|magazine=[[Music & Media]]|date=December 21, 1996|accessdate=November 8, 2018}}</ref>\n|68\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Netherlands (Single Top 100)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dutchcharts.nl/jaaroverzichten.asp?year=1996&cat=s|title=Jaaroverzichten - Single 1996|publisher=[[MegaCharts]]|language=Dutch|accessdate=May 3, 2019}}</ref>\n|83\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Sweden (Sverigetopplistan)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hitlistan.se/netdata/ghl002.mbr/lista?liid=43&dfom=19960001|title=\u00c5rslista Singlar \u2013 \u00c5r 1996|publisher=[[Sverigetopplistan|Topplistan]]|language=Swedish|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150927225923/http://www.hitlistan.se/netdata/ghl002.mbr/lista?liid=43&dfom=19960001|archivedate=September 27, 2015|accessdate=July 2, 2019}}</ref>\n|23\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|US ''Billboard'' Hot 100<ref>{{cite web|url=http://longboredsurfer.com/charts.php?year=1996|title=Billboard Top 100 - 1996|accessdate=August 27, 2010}}</ref>\n|92\n|}\n\n===Certifications===\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Australia|type=single|award=Gold|certyear=1996|relyear=1996|certref=<ref name=\"ausye\"/>}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=New Zealand|artist=Metallica|title=Until It Sleeps|type=single|award=Gold|recent=website|id=3725|relyear=1996|relmonth=05}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Norway|artist=Metallica|title=Until It Sleeps|type=single|award=Gold|relyear=1996}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Sweden|artist=Metallica|title=Until It Sleeps|type=single|award=Gold|certyear=1996|relyear=1996|relmonth=5}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United States|artist=Metallica|title=Until It Sleeps|type=single|award=Gold|relyear=1996|certyear=1996|salesamount=500,000|salesref=<ref>{{cite journal |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=IA8EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA61 |title=Best-Selling Records of 1996 |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=BPI Communications Inc.|date=January 18, 1997 |accessdate=May 8, 2015 |page=61 |issn=0006-2510|volume=109|number=3}}</ref>}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom}}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Release history==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Region\n! scope=\"col\"| Date\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Various\n| May 20, 1996\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| United States\n| May 21, 1996\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Metallica}}\n\n[[Category:Metallica songs]]\n[[Category:1990s ballads]]\n[[Category:1996 singles]]\n[[Category:1996 songs]]\n[[Category:Billboard Mainstream Rock number-one singles]]\n[[Category:American hard rock songs]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Australia]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Denmark]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Finland]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Hungary]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Sweden]]\n[[Category:Songs in memory of deceased persons]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Lars Ulrich]]\n[[Category:Songs written by James Hetfield]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Bob Rock]]\n[[Category:Music videos directed by Samuel Bayer]]\n[[Category:Elektra Records singles]]\n[[Category:Songs about diseases and disorders]]\n[[Category:Songs inspired by deaths]]\n[[Category:Hard rock ballads]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1996 single by Metallica}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2013}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Until It Sleeps\n| cover      = Metallica - Until It Sleeps cover.jpg\n| alt        =\n| border     = yes\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Metallica]]\n| album      = [[Load (album)|Load]]\n| B-side     = {{hlist|\"2 X 4\" (live)|\"F.O.B.D.\" (Demo)|\"[[Kill 'Em All|Kill]]\"|[[Ride the Lightning|\"Ride Medley\" (live)]]|\"Until It Sleeps\" (Herman Melville Mix)|\"Overkill\" (live)}}\n| released   = May 21, 1996<ref>{{cite web|title=Until it Sleeps|url=https://metallica.com/releases/singles-eps/4300/until-it-sleeps|publisher=Metallica.com|accessdate= August 7, 2016}}</ref>\n| format     = {{hlist|[[Gramophone record|7-inch]]|[[CD single|CD]]|[[cassette single|cassette]]}}\n| recorded   = 1995\n| studio     =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Alternative rock]]<ref>{{cite news |last=Jenkins |first=Mark |title=Metallica's 'Re-Load': Bludgeon The Drum Slowly |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/lifestyle/1997/12/03/metallicas-re-load-bludgeon-the-drum-slowly/9b5b8cfc-6576-405c-95f2-62a5cedb3d7a/?noredirect=on |accessdate=February 7, 2019 |work=The Washington Post |date=December 3, 1997}}</ref>|[[hard rock]]}}\n| length     = 4:30\n| label      = [[Elektra Records|Elektra]]\n| writer     = {{hlist|[[James Hetfield]]|[[Lars Ulrich]]}}\n| producer   = {{hlist|[[Bob Rock]]|[[James Hetfield]]|[[Lars Ulrich]]}}\n| prev_title = [[Sad but True]]\n| prev_year  = 1993\n| next_title = [[Hero of the Day]]\n| next_year  = 1996\n| misc       = {{External music video|1={{YouTube|id=MHVv7Mz2_Bo|title=\"Until It Sleeps\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''Until It Sleeps'''\" is a song by American [[heavy metal music|heavy metal]] band [[Metallica]], released on May 21, 1996 as the [[lead single]] from their 1996 album, ''[[Load (album)|Load]]''. It was the band's first number one song on the US ''Billboard'' [[Hot Mainstream Rock Tracks]] chart, as well as their first and only song as of the release of ''[[Hardwired... to Self-Destruct]]'' to hit the top 10 of the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], debuting and peaking at number 10. The song also peaked atop the charts of Australia, Denmark, Finland, Hungary and Sweden.\n\n==Versions==\nThe song was performed with orchestral accompaniment on the album ''[[S&M (Metallica album)|S&M]]''.\n\nAn early demo version of this song was entitled \"F.O.B.D.\" (recorded on December 8, 1995), because it reminded the band members of the Soundgarden song \"[[Fell on Black Days (song)|Fell on Black Days]]\", in that the \"It grips you...It stains you...\" refrain is in the same 6/4 time signature that \"Fell on Black Days\" is in.  The band can be heard saying \"Fell on Black Days\" on the fanclub-only Fancan 1 CD just prior to jamming on a portion of \"Until It Sleeps\". The 10\" vinyl version of the single is red in color.\n\n[[Moby]], credited as \"[[Herman Melville]]\", did an [[industrial music|industrial]]-sounding [[remix]] used as a B-side.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=HpC1D--hcoAC&pg=PA30 Thump 'n Grind]</ref>\n\n\"Until It Sleeps\" became the first \"officially\" pirated [[MP3]] when it was released by Compress \u2019Da Audio (a piracy group and spinoff of the [[Warez scene]]) via an [[Internet Relay Chat]] network on August 10, 1996. An EFnet member on the #mpeg3 IRC channel named Coyote666 was responsible for creating the first mp3 ripping software.<ref name=\"rns\">{{cite web|url=http://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2015/04/27/the-man-who-broke-the-music-business|title=The Man Who Broke the Music Business|last=Witt|first=Stephen|date=April 21, 2015|accessdate=April 24, 2015|work=[[The New Yorker]]}}</ref>\n\n==Lyrics==\nThe lyrics of the song, written by Hetfield, address his mother's battle with cancer, to which the \"it\" in the title refers. They can be seen as either describing the emotional pain he feels for the loss, or the physical pain his mother was feeling while she was ill. Both of his parents were Christian Scientists, and did not believe in medicine. The lyrics are also interpreted as dealing with anger issues. Hetfield's father, Virgil, died in late 1996, during Metallica's Load tour.\n\n==Music video==\nThe song also has a music video directed by [[Samuel Bayer]] ([[Nirvana (band)|Nirvana]], [[Green Day]], [[The Smashing Pumpkins]]). It was shot in various locations around Los Angeles on May 6 and 7 in 1996. It was premiered by [[MTV]] on May 21.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=pw0EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA9 Metallica In For a Lollapalooza of a Summer]</ref> The video depicts [[Surrealism|surreal]] concepts dealing with the fall of man, taken from various paintings by [[Hieronymus Bosch]]. Apart from the general forms inspired from Bosch's paintings, the prominent figures in the video are the human-eating monster from ''[[The Garden of Earthly Delights]]'', the fall of [[Adam (Bible)|Adam]] and [[Eve]] from ''[[Haywain (painting)|Haywain]]'' and Christ in the ''Crucifige Eum'' (Crucify Him) scene of ''[[Ecce Homo]]''.\n\n==Awards==\nThe video of the song won the [[MTV Video Music Award]] for [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Rock Video|Best Rock Video]] in 1996.\n\nThe song won a 1996 [[Metal Edge]] Readers' Choice Award for Song of the Year.<ref>Metal Edge, June 1997</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n|headline = US single\n|title1   = Until It Sleeps\n|length1  = 4:36\n|title2   = Overkill\n|length2  = 4:08\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n|headline = International single part one\n|title1   = Until It Sleeps\n|length1  = 4:33\n|title2   = 2 X 4\n|note2    = Live - Escape from the studio '95\n|length2  = 6:06\n|title3   = F.O.B.D.\n|note3    = aka Until It Sleeps \u2013 early 'writing in progress' version\n|length3  = 4:56\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n|headline = International single part two\n|title1   = Until It Sleeps\n|length1  = 4:36\n|title2   = Kill/Ride Medley \n|note2    = Live - Escape from the studio '95 \n|length2  = 10:19\n|title3   = Until It Sleeps\n|note3    = Herman Melville Mix\n|length3  = 4:20\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n|headline = Japanese EP\n|title1   = Until It Sleeps\n|length1  = 4:35\n|title2   = Until It Sleeps\n|note2    = Herman Melville Mix\n|length2  = 4:22\n|title3   = Kill/Ride Medley\n|note3    = Live - Escape from the studio '95\n|length3  = 10:19\n|title4   = 2 X 4\n|note4    = Live - Escape from the studio '95\n|length4  = 6:08\n|title5   = Overkill\n|note5    = Live\n|length5  = 4:11\n|title6   = F.O.B.D.\n|note6    = aka Until It Sleeps \u2013 early 'writing in progress' version\n|length6  = 4:56\n}}\n\n==Charts and certifications==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n!Chart (1996)\n!Peak<br>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Australia|1|artist=Metallica|song=Until It Sleeps|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Austria|12|artist=Metallica|song=Until It Sleeps|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders|8|artist=Metallica|song=Until It Sleeps|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Wallonia|16|artist=Metallica|song=Until It Sleeps|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Canadatopsingles|5|chartid=9529|rowheader=true|accessdate=May 3, 2019}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Canadarock|6|chartid=3025|rowheader=true|accessdate=May 3, 2019}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Czech Republic ([[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry|IFPI CR]])<ref name=\"m&m\">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/UK/Music-and-Media/90s/1996/MM-1996-06-15.pdf|title=Top National Sellers|magazine=[[Music & Media]]|volume=13|issue=24|page=14|date=June 15, 1996|access-date=February 16, 2020}}</ref>\n|3\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Denmark ([[IFPI Danmark|IFPI]])<ref name=\"m&m\"/>\n|1\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Europe ([[Eurochart Hot 100]])<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Music-and-Media/90s/1996/MM-1996-06-15.pdf|title=Eurochart Hot 100 Singles|magazine=[[Music & Media]]|volume=13|issue=24|page=12|date