ian Mercury |location=Edinburgh |date=28 June 1849 |issue=19897 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Johanna'' \n|flag={{flag|Denmark}}\n|desc=The ship was driven ashore near [[Ringk\u00f8bing]]. She was on a voyage from [[London]], [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland|United Kingdom]] to a port in [[Zealand]].<ref name=CM090749/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Jonge Dirk'' \n|flag={{flag|Netherlands}}\n|desc=The ship was driven ashore near \"Hunshy Kilt\", Denmark. All on board were rescued. She was on a voyage from [[Amsterdam]], [[North Holland]] to [[Rostock]].<ref name=GH130749/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Sally'' \n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The [[schooner]] ran aground off [[Borstahusen]], Sweden. She was refloated the next day and taken in to [[Landscrona]], Sweden.<ref name=CM160749/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==24 June==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=24 June 1849 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Antina Tjakkel'' \n|flag={{flag|Netherlands}}\n|desc=The [[schooner]] was driven ashore and sank at the entrance to the [[Agger Canal]]. Her crew were rescued. She was on a voyage from [[London]], [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland|United Kingdom]] to a Baltic port.<ref name=CM090749/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Providence''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The [[smack (ship)|smack]] was in collision with {{PS|London Merchant|1831|2}} ({{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}) and foundered off the ''[[Mouse Lighthship]]'' ([[File:Trinity House Ensign (pre-1937).svg|22px]] [[Trinity House]]), in the [[North Sea]]. Her crew were rescued.<ref name=Times280649>{{Cite newspaper The Times |articlename=Ship News |date=28 June 1849 |page_number=7 |issue=20214 |column=E }}</ref> She was on a voyage from [[Middlesbrough]], [[North Riding of Yorkshire|Yorkshire]] to [[Rochester, Kent]].<ref name=Times171149>{{Cite newspaper The Times |articlename=Admiralty Court |date=17 November 1849 |page_number=7 |i